---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="LCARS-fleet — zUrp Embedded"
  description="Lightweight Contained Agent Resilient System — multi-agent fleet runtime for Claude Code."
>
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">zUrp Embedded</a>
        <span class="sep">/</span>
        <span class="current">LCARS-fleet</span>
      </p>

      <img
        src="/logo_zUrp-embedded.png"
        alt="zUrp Embedded corporate logotype"
        class="hero-logo"
      />

      <h1>LCARS-fleet</h1>
      <p class="fullname">Lightweight Contained Agent Resilient System</p>

      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge badge-status">⚠ in forge — placeholder</span>
        <span class="badge badge-license">GPL-3.0 on release</span>
        <span class="badge badge-tech">~1 MB of bash</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="pitch">
      <p>
        A multi-agent fleet runtime for Claude Code. ~1&nbsp;MB of plain bash, zero
        framework, NASA-grade corpus discipline. Low-tech agentic orchestration,
        moon-shot quality, built solo.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="invariants">
      <h2>Two load-bearing invariants</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="invariant">
          <div class="invariant-tag">Contained</div>
          <h3>The wall, not the prompt</h3>
          <p>
            The agent runs inside a process boundary enforced by the runtime. Containment
            is a property of the <em>environment</em>, not a request in the prompt.
            Nothing escapes by accident, and nothing escapes by trying.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="invariant">
          <div class="invariant-tag">Resilient</div>
          <h3>Recovery is mechanical</h3>
          <p>
            When an agent fails inside its cell, the runtime detects, isolates, and
            recovers without human intervention. Reprise protocols are encoded in bash,
            not in prayers to an uptime dashboard.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="placeholder-note">
      <h2>🚧 This page is a placeholder</h2>
      <p>
        LCARS-fleet is in active forge — corpus closed, PoCs underway, first release
        targeted for mid-2026. The real code lives in a private repository during this
        phase and will migrate to the public <a href="https://github.com/zUrp-Embedded/LCARS-temp"><code>LCARS-temp</code></a>
        repository on release.
      </p>
      <p>
        This page exists to anchor public links and validate the deployment pipeline.
        Content will grow as the product solidifies — install guide, architecture tour,
        changelog, corpus reference.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container footer-inner">
      <p class="org-link">
        GitHub · <a href="https://github.com/zUrp-Embedded/LCARS-temp">@zUrp-Embedded/LCARS-temp</a>
      </p>
      <p><em>LCARS-fleet — a product of zUrp Embedded, a subsidiary of zUrp Industries.</em></p>
      <p class="legalese">
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, ~1&nbsp;MB of bash, and stubbornness.
        Hosted on GitHub Pages because the cloud is just someone else's keiretsu.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 30%, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 70%, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.05) 0%, transparent 50%),
      var(--bg);
    padding: 4rem 0 5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 32px 32px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .breadcrumb .sep {
    margin: 0 0.5rem;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .breadcrumb .current {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hero-logo {
    max-width: 300px;
    width: 60%;
    filter: invert(1) brightness(1.1);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .fullname {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .badges {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .badge-status {
    background: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.15);
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 1px solid rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.3);
  }

  .badge-license {
    background: rgba(138, 143, 154, 0.1);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .badge-tech {
    background: rgba(138, 143, 154, 0.1);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section {
    padding: 3.5rem 0;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .pitch p {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .invariants {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .invariant {
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .invariant-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .invariant h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .invariant p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .placeholder-note {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .placeholder-note p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .placeholder-note code {
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--fg);
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  footer {
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 3rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .footer-inner p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .org-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem !important;
  }

  .org-link a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .legalese {
    font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
    .fullname {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }
    section {
      padding: 2.5rem 0;
    }
    section h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
